1. New → Ready (Admitted)
When a process is created and admitted into the ready queue.

Reason:
OS accepts the process
Required resources allocated

2. Ready → Running (Scheduler Dispatch)
When CPU is assigned to the process.

Reason:
Short term scheduler selects process
Process starts execution

3. Running → Waiting (I/O or Event Wait)
Process requests I/O or waits for some event.

Reason:
File operation
Device input/output
Resource wait

4. Waiting → Ready (Event Completion)
After the event finishes, the process becomes ready again.

Reason:
I/O completed
Resource available

5. Running → Ready (Interrupt / Time Slice Expired)
Process is interrupted and moved back to ready queue.

Reason:
Time quantum finished (Round Robin)
Higher priority process arrived

6. Running → Terminated (Exit)
Process finishes execution.

Reason:
Program completed
Process killed
Fatal error
